00023 static std::vector<bool>
00024 build_noop_index(const std::vector <std::pair <size_t, size_t> > &noops)
00025 {
00026     /* Sort subsequences into buckets by length */
00027     size_t retval_size = 0;
00028     std::map<size_t/*size*/, std::vector <size_t/*offset*/> > sorted;
00029     for (std::vector<std::pair<size_t, size_t> >::const_iterator ni=noops.begin(); ni!=noops.end(); ++ni) {
00030         sorted[(*ni).second].push_back((*ni).first);
00031         retval_size = std::max(retval_size, (*ni).first + (*ni).second);
00032     }
00033     
00034     /* Allocate a return value */
00035     if (0==retval_size) {
00036         std::vector<bool> empty;
00037         return empty;
00038     }
00039     std::vector<bool> retval(retval_size, false);
00040 
00041     /* Process in order from largest to smallest */
00042     for (std::map<size_t, std::vector<size_t> >::reverse_iterator szi=sorted.rbegin(); szi!=sorted.rend(); ++szi) {
00043         size_t sz = (*szi).first;
00044         for (std::vector<size_t>::const_iterator idxi=(*szi).second.begin(); idxi<(*szi).second.end(); ++idxi) {
00045             size_t idx = *idxi;
00046             
00047             /* Are any instructions in this range already marked as no-ops?  If so, then skip this one. */
00048             bool overlaps = false;
00049             for (size_t i=0; i<sz && !overlaps; ++i)
00050                 overlaps = retval[idx+i];
00051             if (overlaps)
00052                 continue;
00053             
00054             /* Mark these instructions as no-ops */
00055             for (size_t i=0; i<sz; ++i)
00056                 retval[idx+i] = true;
00057         }
00058     }
00059     
00060     return retval;
00061 }

00178 bool
00179 AsmUnparser::is_unparsable_node(SgNode *node)
00180 {
00181     if (isSgAsmFunction(node) || isSgAsmInstruction(node) || isSgAsmStaticData(node) || isSgAsmInterpretation(node))
00182         return true;
00183 
00184     SgAsmBlock *block = isSgAsmBlock(node);
00185     if (block!=NULL) {
00186         const SgAsmStatementPtrList &stmts = block->get_statementList();
00187         if (!stmts.empty() &&
00188             (isSgAsmInstruction(stmts.front()) || isSgAsmStaticData(stmts.front())))
00189             return true;
00190     }
00191 
00192     return false;
00193 }

00195 SgNode *
00196 AsmUnparser::find_unparsable_node(SgNode *ast)
00197 {
00198     SgNode *root = NULL;
00199     try {
00200         struct T1: public SgSimpleProcessing {
00201             AsmUnparser *unparser;
00202             T1(AsmUnparser *unparser): unparser(unparser) {}
00203             void visit(SgNode *node) {
00204                 if (unparser->is_unparsable_node(node))
00205                     throw node;

00215 std::vector<SgNode*>
00216 AsmUnparser::find_unparsable_nodes(SgNode *ast)
00217 {
00218     struct T1: public AstPrePostProcessing {
00219         AsmUnparser *unparser;
00220         SgNode *ignore;
00221         std::vector<SgNode*> found;
00222         T1(AsmUnparser *unparser): unparser(unparser), ignore(NULL) {}
00223         void preOrderVisit(SgNode *node) {
00224             if (!ignore && unparser->is_unparsable_node(node)) {
00225                 found.push_back(node);
00226                 ignore = node;
00227             }
00228         }
00229         void postOrderVisit(SgNode *node) {
00230             if (ignore==node)
00231                 ignore = NULL;
00232         }
00233     } t1(this);
00234     t1.traverse(ast);
00235     return t1.found;
00236 }

00238 void
00239 AsmUnparser::start_of_object(rose_addr_t va, std::ostream &output)
00240 {
00241     if (skipback.active && ORGANIZED_BY_ADDRESS==organization) {
00242         if (skipback.triggered) {
00243             if (va > skipback.va) {
00244                 rose_addr_t nskipped = va - skipback.va;
00245                 output <<"Skipping " <<nskipped <<" byte" <<(1==nskipped?"":"s") <<"\n";
00246             } else if (va < skipback.va) {
00247                 rose_addr_t nback = skipback.va - va;
00248                 output <<"Backward " <<nback <<" byte" <<(1==nback?"":"s") <<"\n";
00249             }
00250         }
00251         skipback.triggered = true;
00252     }
00253 }

00280 size_t
00281 AsmUnparser::unparse(std::ostream &output, SgNode *ast)
00282 {
00283     size_t retval = 0;
00284 
00285     switch (get_organization()) {
00286         case ORGANIZED_BY_AST: {
00287             std::vector<SgNode*> unparsable = find_unparsable_nodes(ast);
00288             for (std::vector<SgNode*>::iterator ui=unparsable.begin(); ui!=unparsable.end(); ++ui)
00289                 unparse_one_node(output, *ui);
00290             retval = unparsable.size();
00291             break;
00292         }
00293 
00294 
00295         case ORGANIZED_BY_ADDRESS: {
00296             typedef std::multimap<rose_addr_t, SgAsmStatement*> StatementMap;
00297             struct GatherStatements: public AstSimpleProcessing {
00298                 StatementMap *stmts;
00299                 GatherStatements(StatementMap *stmts): stmts(stmts) {}
00300                 void visit(SgNode *node) {
00301                     if (isSgAsmInstruction(node) || isSgAsmStaticData(node)) {
00302                         SgAsmStatement *stmt = isSgAsmStatement(node);
00303                         assert(stmt!=NULL);
00304                         stmts->insert(std::make_pair(stmt->get_address(), stmt));
00305                     }
00306                 }
00307             };
00308             StatementMap stmts;
00309             GatherStatements(&stmts).traverse(ast, preorder);
00310             for (StatementMap::iterator si=stmts.begin(); si!=stmts.end(); ++si)
00311                 unparse_one_node(output, si->second);
00312             retval = stmts.size();
00313             break;
00314         }
00315 
00316         // no default since it would prevent compiler warnings
00317     }
00318     return retval;
00319 }

00321 bool
00322 AsmUnparser::unparse_one_node(std::ostream &output, SgNode *node)
00323 {
00324     SgAsmInstruction *insn = isSgAsmInstruction(node);
00325     if (insn)
00326         return unparse_insn(true, output, insn, (size_t)(-1));
00327 
00328     SgAsmStaticData *data = isSgAsmStaticData(node);
00329     if (data)
00330         return unparse_staticdata(true, output, data, (size_t)(-1));
00331 
00332     SgAsmBlock *block = isSgAsmBlock(node);
00333     if (block) {
00334         const SgAsmStatementPtrList &stmts = block->get_statementList();
00335         assert(!stmts.empty());
00336         if (isSgAsmInstruction(stmts.front())) {
00337             return unparse_basicblock(true, output, block);
00338         } else if (isSgAsmStaticData(stmts.front())) {
00339             return unparse_datablock(true, output, block);
00340         }
00341     }
00342 
00343     SgAsmFunction *func = isSgAsmFunction(node);
00344     if (func)
00345         return unparse_function(true, output, func);
00346 
00347     SgAsmInterpretation *interp = isSgAsmInterpretation(node);
00348     if (interp)
00349         return unparse_interpretation(true, output, interp);
00350 
00351     return false;
00352 }

00498 bool
00499 AsmUnparser::InsnBlockEntry::operator()(bool enabled, const InsnArgs &args)
00500 {
00501     if (enabled && ORGANIZED_BY_ADDRESS==args.unparser->get_organization()) {
00502         SgAsmBlock *block = isSgAsmBlock(args.insn->get_parent()); // look only to immediate parent
00503         bool is_first_insn = block && args.insn==block->get_statementList().front();
00504 
00505         static size_t width = 0;
00506         if (0==width)
00507             width = block->reason_str(true, 0).size();
00508 
00509         if (show_function) {
00510             SgAsmFunction *func = SageInterface::getEnclosingNode<SgAsmFunction>(block);
00511             char buf[32];
00512             if (func && is_first_insn) {
00513                 snprintf(buf, sizeof buf, "F%08"PRIx64, func->get_entry_va());
00514             } else {
00515                 sprintf(buf, "%*s", 9, "");
00516             }
00517             args.output <<" " <<buf;
00518         }
00519 
00520         if (show_reasons) {
00521             if (block && is_first_insn) {
00522                 args.output <<" " <<block->reason_str(true) <<" ";
00523             } else {
00524                 args.output <<std::setw(width+2) <<" ";
00525             }
00526         }
00527     }
00528     return enabled;

00582         typedef std::vector<std::pair<size_t, size_t> > NoopSequences; /* array of index,size pairs */

00601         if (bmi!=args.unparser->cfg_blockmap.end()) {
00602             CFG_Vertex vertex = bmi->second;
00603             size_t npreds = 0;
00604             SgAsmFunction *my_func = args.block->get_enclosing_function();
00605             boost::graph_traits<CFG>::in_edge_iterator ei, ei_end;
00606             for (boost::tie(ei, ei_end)=in_edges(vertex, args.unparser->cfg); ei!=ei_end; ++ei) {
00607                 SgAsmBlock *pred_blk = get(boost::vertex_name, args.unparser->cfg, source(*ei, args.unparser->cfg));
00608                 SgAsmFunction *pred_func = pred_blk ? pred_blk->get_enclosing_function() : NULL;
00609                 if (pred_blk) {
00610                     if (0==npreds++) {
00611                         args.output <<args.unparser->line_prefix() <<"Predecessor blocks: ";
00612                     } else {
00613                         args.output <<", ";
00614                     }
00615                     args.output <<StringUtility::addrToString(pred_blk->get_address());
00616                     if (pred_func && my_func && pred_func!=my_func) {
00617                         if (pred_func->get_name().empty()) {
00618                             args.output <<"<<Func>>";
00619                         } else {
00620                             args.output <<"<" <<pred_func->get_name() <<">";
00621                         }
00622                     }
00623                 }
00624             }
00625             if (npreds>0)
00626                 args.output <<"\n";
00627         }
00628     }
00629     return enabled;
00630 }

00671 bool
00672 AsmUnparser::BasicBlockSuccessors::operator()(bool enabled, const BasicBlockArgs &args)
00673 {
00674     if (enabled) {
00675             size_t nsucs = 0;
00676             args.output <<args.unparser->line_prefix() <<"Successor blocks: ";
00677         SgAsmFunction *my_func = args.block->get_enclosing_function();
00678 
00679         CFG_BlockMap::const_iterator bmi = args.unparser->cfg_blockmap.find(args.block);
00680         if (bmi!=args.unparser->cfg_blockmap.end()) {
00681             // Use the unparser's CFG if it contains info for this block.
00682             CFG_Vertex vertex = bmi->second;
00683             boost::graph_traits<CFG>::out_edge_iterator ei, ei_end;
00684             for (boost::tie(ei, ei_end)=out_edges(vertex, args.unparser->cfg); ei!=ei_end; ++ei) {
00685                 SgAsmBlock *suc_blk = get(boost::vertex_name, args.unparser->cfg, target(*ei, args.unparser->cfg));
00686                 SgAsmFunction *suc_func = suc_blk->get_enclosing_function();
00687                 if (suc_blk) {
00688                     args.output <<(0==nsucs++?"":", ") <<StringUtility::addrToString(suc_blk->get_address());
00689                     if (suc_func && my_func && suc_func!=my_func) {
00690                         if (suc_blk->get_address() != suc_func->get_entry_va())
00691                             args.output <<" in ";
00692                         if (suc_func->get_name().empty()) {
00693                             args.output <<"<<Func>>";
00694                         } else {
00695                             args.output <<"<" <<suc_func->get_name() <<">";
00696                         }
00697                     }
00698                 }
00699             }
00700         } else {
00701             // Use the successors cached in the AST. We print them as absolute virtual addresses rather than using
00702             // SgAsmIntegerValueExpression::get_label() because the value would probably have already been printed using
00703             // get_label() in the previous disassembled instruction.
00704             const SgAsmIntegerValuePtrList &successors = args.block->get_successors();
00705             for (SgAsmIntegerValuePtrList::const_iterator si=successors.begin(); si!=successors.end(); ++si) {
00706                 args.output <<(0==nsucs++?"":", ") <<StringUtility::addrToString((*si)->get_absolute_value());
00707                 SgAsmBlock *suc_blk = isSgAsmBlock((*si)->get_base_node());
00708                 SgAsmFunction *suc_func = suc_blk ? suc_blk->get_enclosing_function() : isSgAsmFunction((*si)->get_base_node());
00709                 if (suc_func && my_func && suc_func!=my_func) {
00710                     if (suc_func->get_entry_va() != (*si)->get_absolute_value())
00711                         args.output <<" in ";
00712                     if (suc_func->get_name().empty()) {
00713                         args.output <<"<<Func>>";
00714                     } else {
00715                         args.output <<"<" <<suc_func->get_name() <<">";
00716                     }
00717                 }
00718             }
00719         }
00720 
00721         // The control flow graph doesn't store whether successor information is complete or not.  We have no choice but to get
00722         // that tidbit from the AST.
00723         if (!args.block->get_successors_complete())
00724             args.output <<(0==nsucs++?"":", ") <<"unknown";
00725         args.output <<(0==nsucs?"none\n":"\n");
00726     }
00727     return enabled;
00728 }

00771 AsmUnparser::StaticDataBlockEntry::operator()(bool enabled, const StaticDataArgs &args)
00772 {
00773     if (enabled && ORGANIZED_BY_ADDRESS==args.unparser->get_organization()) {
00774         SgAsmBlock *block = isSgAsmBlock(args.data->get_parent()); // look only to immediate parent
00775         bool is_first_data = block && args.data==block->get_statementList().front();
00776 
00777         static size_t width = 0;
00778         if (0==width)
00779             width = block->reason_str(true, 0).size();
00780 
00781         if (show_function) {

00783             char buf[32];

00791 
00792         if (show_reasons) {
00793             if (block && is_first_data) {
00794                 args.output <<" " <<block->reason_str(true) <<" ";

00796                 args.output <<std::setw(width+2) <<" ";
00797             }
00798         }
00799     }

00805 {
00806     rose_addr_t start_address = 0;
00807     char prefix[64], *addr_fmt=NULL;

00809

00828             args.output <<tmp_fmt.prefix;
00829 
00830         SgAsmExecutableFileFormat::hexdump(args.output, start_address, &(args.data->get_raw_bytes()[0]),
00831                                            args.data->get_size(), tmp_fmt);

00900 bool
00901 AsmUnparser::StaticDataDisassembler::operator()(bool enabled, const StaticDataArgs &args)
00902 {
00903     SgAsmBlock *block = SageInterface::getEnclosingNode<SgAsmBlock>(args.data);
00904     if (enabled && block && disassembler && unparser &&
00905         0==(block->get_reason() & SgAsmBlock::BLK_PADDING) &&
00906         0==(block->get_reason() & SgAsmBlock::BLK_JUMPTABLE)) {
00907         SgUnsignedCharList data = args.data->get_raw_bytes();
00908         MemoryMap map;
00909         map.insert(Extent(args.data->get_address(), data.size()),
00910                    MemoryMap::Segment(MemoryMap::ExternBuffer::create(&data[0], data.size()), 0,
00911                                       MemoryMap::MM_PROT_RX, "static data block"));
00912         Disassembler::AddressSet worklist;
00913         worklist.insert(args.data->get_address());
00914         Disassembler::BadMap bad;
00915         Disassembler::InstructionMap insns = disassembler->disassembleBuffer(&map, worklist, NULL, &bad);
00916         unparser->set_prefix_format(args.unparser->get_prefix_format());
00917         for (Disassembler::InstructionMap::iterator ii=insns.begin(); ii!=insns.end(); ++ii) {
00918             unparser->unparse(args.output, ii->second);
00919             SageInterface::deleteAST(ii->second);
00920         }
00921     }
00922     return enabled;
00923 }
